reviews.review_text: Glory If you're like me, then searching for new shows to listen to can feel like an absolutely endless (while optimistic and wholesome) labor of love. However, I would never complain, because the archive has blessed us with the opportunity to not just hear everything, but what's in between everything, too. The Dead were always about human connection, and that philosophy has carried their fan base into a completely liquid environment. I would include myself in that category - regardless of never seeing Pigpen, Keith, Jerry, or Brent. The world's at my fingertips. Although, beside aLL of that - the discovery of new elements (or, just what some years sounded like compared to others) is exactly what's been presented here in stunning quality above what else I've heard. So far, the music is played Lightning quick, words even remembered, and it's palatable from the very first impression. You can't go wrong with anything here. Trust me, audience tapes are supposed to sound this open, as if you're actuaLLy in the arena. Don't be scared! Imagine you're dancing along with thousands of your closest friends. * Zap!
